children.text: There have not been noggings or trimmers installed between the trusses at the change of direction areas to pick up and support the ceiling plasterboard sheets.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
It is a requirement of the plasterboard manufacturer, that

‘Where sheets are fixed directly to structural ceiling members. If plasterboard is direct fixed to structural ceiling members, trimmers are to be installed by the builder where primary ceiling support members such as girder trusses and joists change direction within a room’ .
Additionally, Australian Standard AS 4440 Installation of Nail-plated Timber Roof Trusses, states in section 3.5 Plasterboard fixed directly to bottom chords, that

‘Where plasterboard is fixed directly to the bottom chord of trusses, supplementary noggings shall be fitted where the bottom chords of the hip-end system do not continue to run parallel to the main run of trusses. They shall be fixed at a spacing required by the plasterboard manufacturer’ .
Trimmers or noggings will need to be installed in the change of direction areas, so that the ceiling plasterboard sheets can be securely fixed to the framing at their required centres.
